<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="335" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12581: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-23T18:00:00+00:00">December 23, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 23—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6447. Reference your 6723, December 21, 7 p.m.<note n="19" xml:id="d335fn19">Not printed.</note> When telegraphing to the
                            Department joint telegrams from the Allied Ministers at Jassy, this
                            Embassy has automatically sent copies to the American Mission. This
                            custom has also been followed with all telegrams and other
                            communications containing information which is thought to be of interest
                            to the Mission. See my 6144, December 5, 7 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d335fn20">
                                <ref target="frus1919Parisv01#pg_205">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 205</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>